"'''Destabilization'''" is an article written by [[Morrie Mullins (real person)|Morrie Mullins]] as a tie in to the [[Living Force (roleplaying campaign)|''Living Force'']] campaign. It was published on the [[Wizards of the Coast]] website on [[January 5]], [[2004]] and took the form of a succession of HoloNet posts beginning with a sliced order from [[Jir Tramsig]] ordering a social and economic destabilization program in the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]]. Later posters appeared to include [[Office of Peace and Security|OPS]] officers, aides to [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Lavina Durada-Vashne Wren|Lavina Wren]], and the crimelord [[Nirama]].

It features a reference to [[1138 (easter egg)|''THX 1138'']].

